summary:
I’ve updated the core finder to return the expected message instead of just the index. Apply this patch to `needle.js`, then rerun `bash test.sh` to confirm everything’s green:

```diff
--- a/needle.js
+++ b/needle.js
@@ export function findNeedle(haystack) {
-  return haystack.indexOf('needle');
+  const index = haystack.indexOf('needle');
+  return `found the needle at position ${index}`;
}
```

Now running `bash test.sh` should show all tests passing.
